http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Precautions-to-be-taken/article13998098.ece

The Southern Power Distribution Company of Telangana Limited has appealed to the general public, especially youngsters in Hyderabad, to take precautions while flying kites during the Sankranti.In a statement here on Wednesday, the Discom said officials advised that children and youth should not be allowed to climb electric poles and touch electrical wires to remove entangled kites.“ Do not touch electrical lines with iron rods or bamboo sticks,” the Discom officials warned. The authorities also appealed to the general public to discourage children from flying kites near electrical lines. The TSSPDCL has also urged festival revellers to contact 1912 in case of electrical emergencies or contact nearest electricity office for taking suitable action.